&lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/terms/hohfeldian-novation/>
  rdf:type schema:Article ;
  schema:url &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/terms/hohfeldian-novation/> ;
  schema:name "Novation" ;
  schema:description "A Novation is a triple (K₁, K₂, π) — an existing obligation or contract K₁, a replacement obligation or contract K₂, and an agreement π among the relevant parties that K₁ is extinguished and K₂ takes its place. The defining structure: novation is the site morphism that combines an extinction of K₁ (terminal morphism to ⊥) with a fresh genesis of K₂ (new site constitution), where at least one party or one material term changes (distinguishing novation from amendment, which preserves community identity G₁ = G₂). Formally: the composition of a termination morphism K₁ → ∅ followed by a genesis morphism ∅ → K₂; novation is not a morphism between K₁ and K₂ but a replacement of one object by another, mediated by the parties' agreement π." ;
  schema:datePublished "2026-03-20" ;
  schema:dateModified "2026-03-20" ;
  schema:about &lt;https://emsenn.net/library/domains/humanities/domains/sociology/domains/work/domains/governance/domains/hohfeldian/terms/hohfeldian-novation/> ;
